Join a team whose mission is to develop unique, innovative solutions for Xeon, Xeon test, Cluster Health Management, software optimization for Xeon, Cloud engineering (including virtualization / containers / hypervisors) and more. 
 
If you are passionate about creating solutions and technical pathfinding and, are passionate about writing, testing and deploying software as part of a high performing team, please apply and let's have a chat about you and the team and how this might be the best opportunity for you in 2021. 
 
Please apply if you're excited to hear more about what we have to offer. 
 
The ideal candidate is a passionate Technologist who exhibits the following traits: 
Demonstrable coding skills, including cloud and platform solutions. 
Significant leadership of programs, projects and initiatives 
Strong background in collaborative project execution as part of a product team. 
Fast learner with the capability to synthesize and communicate new innovations 
Qualifications 
Bachelor of Science Computer Science or related field 
15+ years of experience in platform and/or cloud software. 
Software development in C or the Rust programming language 
Xeon / x86 architecture 
Xeon platform design and architecture 
Cluster Server technologies - orchestration, virtualization, containers 
Linux environment and development skills 
Inside this Business Group 
The Data Platforms Engineering and Architecture (DPEA) Group invents, designs & builds the world's most critical computing platforms which fuel Intel's most important business and solve the world's most fundamental problems. DPEA enables that data center which is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologiesâ€”spanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutionsâ€”that fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world. 
